Question 37.Question:
A given volume of methane diffuses in 20s. How long will it take the same volume of sulphur (IV) oxide to diffuse under the same conditions?

[C = 12, H = 1, S = 32, O = 16]
Question 37.Explanation:
R1/R2 = √d2/d1 = √M2/M1

Where R = rate of diffusion, d = vapour density, and M = molecular mass

R = volume/time

Calculating R, we get

(VCH4/TCH4)/(Vso4/TSO4)

= √Mso2/MCH4

= (v/20)/(vol/t)

= √64/16

= (vol/20) x (time/vol).

= 8/4

Time = 8 x (20/4)

= 40s
